premise_source_doc_sentence: William Jennings Bryan  (  March 19 , 1860 -- July 26 , 1925  )  was an American orator and politician from Nebraska , and a dominant force in the populist wing of the Democratic Party , standing three times as the Party 's nominee for President of the United States  (  1896 , 1900 , and 1908  )  .
